        "content": "*\u201cEven in Tulum\u2019s transient flow, we are planting seeds of regeneration\u2014one ride, one event, one connection at a time\u201d*\n\n### **Founding Story & Key Motivations**\n\nReFi Tulum sprouted from conversations between Sandra Ponce de Leon and John Daas, driven by their shared belief in the regenerative finance movement and inspired by the possibilities of Gitcoin\u2019s funding ecosystem. As Tulum\u2019s vibrant energy draws a mix of locals, digital nomads, and travellers, Sandra saw an opportunity to embed ReFi into the heart of this eco-conscious but transient community.\n\nHer mission was clear: create practical, locally driven regenerative projects while amplifying the visibility of women and underrepresented voices in the ReFi movement.\n\n### **What Makes ReFi Tulum Special**\n\nTulum\u2019s unique ecosystem of natural beauty, sustainability-minded locals, and global travellers makes it an ideal testing ground for innovative, place-based regeneration models. What sets ReFi Tulum apart is its commitment to combining **community action with visibility**: creating tangible, on-the-ground solutions like **ReFi Rides**, while also championing the **Fierce Feminine of ReFi** at global events.\n\nDespite the challenges of a transient population and stretched resources, ReFi Tulum is proof that even small nodes can drive meaningful impact\u2014connecting local actions to a global movement.\n\n![GVcD9-3W0AMpJJA.jpeg](nodes/refi-tulum/images/cover.jpeg)\n\n## 2024 Highlights\n\n### Hosting Events & Earth Day Commitments\n\n- **What Happened:** ReFi Tulum committed to monthly Earth Day participation, alongside various community events to engage locals and visitors. These gatherings created spaces to discuss regenerative principles and onboard people into ReFi initiatives.\n- **Why It Matters:** With Tulum\u2019s transient population, consistent events are critical for maintaining visibility and fostering interest in ReFi among locals and the global audience visiting the region.\n\n### Launch of ReFi Rides\n\n- **What Happened:** ReFi Tulum launched **ReFi Rides**, an eco-friendly transportation initiative aimed at blending sustainability and community engagement.\n- **Why It Matters:** ReFi Rides serves as a practical example of regeneration in action, offering a tangible solution that aligns with Tulum\u2019s eco-conscious identity while introducing ReFi principles to a broader audience.\n\n### Strategic Partnerships\n\n- **What Happened:** Built partnerships with **Tulum Circula**, **Petgas**, local restaurants, and potential collaborators like **Puntos Limpios**, **LetsGrowDAO**, and **ProductShare**.\n- **Why It Matters:** Collaborating with established local and global organizations amplifies ReFi Tulum\u2019s reach, provides shared resources, and creates new opportunities for growth. Partnerships are key to overcoming resource constraints and scaling impact.\n\n### Amplifying the Fierce Feminine of ReFi\n\n- **What Happened:** Sandra represented ReFi Tulum at major events including **ETHMexico**, **DAOashe in Madrid**, and **Art Basel**, showcasing the contributions of women in the regenerative movement.\n- **Why It Matters:** Bringing ReFi Tulum\u2019s voice to global stages promotes the node\u2019s work, inspires participation, and highlights underrepresented leadership in the ReFi ecosystem.\n\n## Vision for 2025\n\n### Strengthen Community Engagement & Membership\n\n- **What\u2019s Coming:** Develop onboarding systems, improve engagement strategies, and focus on partnerships to create a stable, core community.\n- **Why It Matters:** Overcoming Tulum\u2019s transient nature requires a solid community foundation. Building committed local members will provide the node with greater resilience and continuity.\n\n### Scale ReFi Rides\n\n- **What\u2019s Coming:** Expand the ReFi Rides initiative to reach more users, integrating NFTs and partnerships to enhance sustainability and create a viable revenue stream.\n- **Why It Matters:** Scaling ReFi Rides turns it into a flagship project that showcases how regeneration can be practical, community-driven, and financially sustainable.\n\n### **Deepen Partnerships for Growth**\n\n- **What\u2019s Coming:** Strengthen collaborations with local businesses and organisations like Tulum Circula and Puntos Limpios, while forging alliances with global ReFi nodes.\n- **Why It Matters:** Stronger partnerships will bring resources, visibility, and technical support, helping ReFi Tulum scale its efforts and build credibility within the ecosystem.\n\n### Formalise Organizational Structure\n\n- **What\u2019s Coming:** Establish a clear DAO or governance structure to streamline decision-making, allocate resources, and create transparency for contributors and partners.\n- **Why It Matters:** A formal structure will provide clarity, accountability, and the foundation needed to attract funding, scale operations, and manage projects effectively.\n\n![GMlPVdgXIAAMCc5.jpeg](nodes/refi-tulum/images/refi-tulum6.jpeg)\n\n![Gem4LJiXUAAhnnO.jpeg](nodes/refi-tulum/images/refi-tulum4.jpeg)\n\n![GLkzCpoXoAACejH.jpeg](nodes/refi-tulum/images/refi-tulum5.jpeg)\n\n![GbtVACPWsAUwQ9l.jpeg](nodes/refi-tulum/images/refi-tulum3.jpeg)\n\n![GbboD39awAAhe6R.jpeg](nodes/refi-tulum/images/refi-tulum2.jpeg)\n\n![GbboAFxakAElwJw.jpeg](nodes/refi-tulum/images/refi-tulum1.jpeg)\n\n![GWyp94fXQAEYeqr.jpeg](nodes/refi-tulum/images/refi-tulum7.jpeg)\n\n![GYLl0fyX0AAVJVi.jpeg](nodes/refi-tulum/images/refi-tulum8.jpeg)"
